MriWatcher 2.1 (Jan 10, 2012) -- nitrc svn revision 10 

New Features:

- add drag and drop functions for opening images and make an overlay.

- add command line functions for calling MriWatcher(some options are different with qt3's MriWatcher to follow the tradition of Unix).

Type --help to get the following instructions:
>./MriWatcher --help

Grey level images' viewer.
Usage: MriWatcher [GreyScaleImages]... [OPTIONS]...

OPTIONS
  -A, --viewAll 		 set view options to view all images
  -m, --intensityMin <arg> 	 set intensity minimum of all images
  -M, --intensityMax <arg> 	 set intensity maximum of all images
  -o, --overlayImage <file> 	 load overlay image
  --overlayAlpha <arg> 		 set alpha of overlay image
  --quit 			 just quit MriWatcher
  -s, --snapshot <file> 	 set snapshot image name and save snapshot
  --title <arg> 		 set MriWatcher main window's title
  --help 			 display this help and exit
  --version 			 output MriWatcher version information and exit

- add new logo and quick tips

- add version number and release notes


Fixed Issues:

- slice blending checkbox reverse

